Description: Egyptian terracotta female figure, possibly pregnant. Bottom half is missing. Mould-made and hollow. Brown Nile silt fabric with abundant fine gold mica, quartz and white inclusions.
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Museum of Classical Archaeology, Cambridge. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.

Small and simple hollow terracotta figure of a woman. Probably locally made and of Ptolemaic date. Very similar in style to Cambridge, Museum of Classical Archaeology NA513 and NA678. Gutch dates NA678 to 150BC to 250AD (Gutch in Hogarth 1899, pl.12, no.149).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (DD.433) (Phase 1)
